        "timestamp": "2019-03-26 16:16:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSeems ok. just wondering about one thing:\nwhen you register: in a loop and get everything in results variable, does each result item also contain the \"item\" containing the loop item that the result was for? it seems so, but I cannot find anything in docs, at least nothing explicit.\nAnd btw, maybe I don't understand something, but why do you have such giant loops here? Actually I would guess that all resources should just be extracted to one target place, and you should not be able to specify different targets for each. It would simplify many things then. I see that currently aux resources must be docker images, othervise the world explodes. for example if someone would also want some npm stuff there, no no.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
